# read data from .csv files
data_HC, nodenames = readdlm("HC_ROI_bold_readings.csv", ',', Float64, '\n'; header=true)
data_MS, nodenames = readdlm("MS_ROI_bold_readings.csv", ',', Float64, '\n'; header=true)

# extract time stamps in last column
time_HC = data_HC[:, end]
time_MS = data_MS[:, end]

# remove the first and the last columns from data_*
nodenames = nodenames[2:end-1]

HCT1 = data_HC[T1ind(time_HC), 2:end-1]
HCT2 = data_HC[T2ind(time_HC), 2:end-1]
HCT3 = data_HC[T3ind(time_HC), 2:end-1]
MST1 = data_MS[T1ind(time_MS), 2:end-1]
MST2 = data_MS[T2ind(time_MS), 2:end-1]
MST3 = data_MS[T3ind(time_MS), 2:end-1]

# center each sample
HCT1 = center(HCT1)
HCT2 = center(HCT2)
HCT3 = center(HCT3)
MST1 = center(MST1)
MST2 = center(MST2)
MST3 = center(MST3);

Simultaneous equal graph tests¶

In [5]:
function linear(X)
    m, n = size(X)
    p = div(m * (m + 1), 2)
    out = zeros(Float64, p, n)
    for i = 1:n
        ind = 0
        for row = 1:m
            for col = 1:row
                ind += 1
                out[ind,i] = X[col,i]*X[row,i]
            end
        end
    end
    out
end

function trimap(i, j; diagonal=true)
    if i > j
        return trimap(j, i)
    else
        return i + div(j * (j - 1), 2)
    end
end

function itrimap(k; diagonal=true)
    j = convert(Int, ceil((-1. + sqrt(1. + 8. * k)) / 2.))
    i = k - div(j * (j - 1), 2)
    CartesianIndex(i, j)
end

function unpack(; diagonal=true)
    p = length()
    m = convert(Int, ceil((-1. + sqrt(1. + 8. * p)) / 2.))
    out = zeros(m, m)
    for k = 1:p
        out[itrimap(k, diagonal=true)] = [k]
    end
    out + out' - diagm(diag(out))
end

# pre-specified ROIs
ROIs = ["Precentral_L","Frontal_Sup_Orb_L","Frontal_Sup_Orb_R","Frontal_Mid_L","Frontal_Mid_Orb_L","Olfactory_L",
    "Olfactory_R","Frontal_Med_Orb_L","Frontal_Med_Orb_R","Rectus_L","Rectus_R","Hippocampus_R","Amygdala_L",
    "Parietal_Inf_L","SupraMarginal_L","Paracentral_Lobule_L","Pallidum_L","Cerebelum_Crus2_R","Cerebelum_3_L",
    "Cerebelum_3_R","Cerebelum_10_L","Cerebelum_10_R","Vermis_1_2","Vermis_6","Vermis_10"]

nROIs = length(ROIs)

ROIs_ind = zeros(Int, nROIs)
for i = 1:nROIs
    ROIs_ind[i] = findfirst(isequal(ROIs[i]), nodenames)
end
sort!(ROIs_ind)

_ind = zeros(Int, div(nROIs * (nROIs + 1), 2))
k = 0
for j = 1:nROIs
    for i = 1:j
        k += 1
        _ind[k] = trimap(ROIs_ind[i], ROIs_ind[j], diagonal=true)
    end
end

HCT1 = linear(HCT1')
HCT2 = linear(HCT2')
HCT3 = linear(HCT3')
MST1 = linear(MST1')
MST2 = linear(MST2')
MST3 = linear(MST3')

p, nHCT1 = size(HCT1)
nHCT2 = size(HCT2, 2)
nHCT3 = size(HCT3, 2)
nMST1 = size(MST1, 2)
nMST2 = size(MST2, 2)
nMST3 = size(MST3, 2)

function equal_graph_test(x, y)
    p, nx = size(x)
    ny = size(y, 2)
    
    println("step 1")
    1 = 1.01 * quantile(Normal(), 1. - 0.05 / p)
     = spKLIEP(x, y, 1, CD_KLIEP(); loadings=true)
    
    println("step 2")
    2 = sqrt(2. * log(p) / ny)
    H = KLIEP_Hessian(spzeros(Float64, p), y)
    Hinv = Vector{SparseIterate{Float64}}(undef, length(_ind))
    for k in 1:length(_ind)
         = Hinv_row(H, _ind[k], 2)
        
        supp = KLIEPInference._find_supp(_ind[k], )
        h = view(H, supp, supp)
         = (supp .== _ind[k])
        [supp] = h\
        
        Hinv[k] = 
    end
    
    println("step 3 + bootstrap...")
    boot = boot_SparKLIE(x, y, , Hinv, _ind; debias=1)
    
    CI = simulCI(boot, 0.05)
    
    boot.hat .* broadcast(|, CI[:,1] .> 0., CI[:,2] .< 0.)
end
